Issues.Body:
### Description

In WinForms, I created an Outlook VSTO Add-in project and added a FormRegion and a UserControl. I loaded the FormRegion into the adjoining region of the mail message window and the UserControl into the Custom Task pane. The FormRegion remains visible and functions as expected. But when calling  the Graphics.MeasureString method inside the UserControl.InitializeComponent method, the FormRegion disappears.

```
//User control's InitializeComponent method. 
 private void InitializeComponent()
 {
     this.SuspendLayout();
     // 
     // MyPane
     // 
// Calling the Graphics.MeasureString method.
     this.CreateGraphics().MeasureString("A-Text", Font,24,new StringFormat());
     this.AutoScaleDimensions = new System.Drawing.SizeF(8F, 16F);
     this.AutoScaleMode = System.Windows.Forms.AutoScaleMode.Font;   
     this.Name = "MyPane";
     this.Size = new System.Drawing.Size(543, 337);
     this.ResumeLayout(false);
 }
```

### Reproduction Steps

1. Create a WinForms Outlook VSTO Add-in project.
2. Add the FormRegion to the adjoining region in the Mail Message window.
3. Add  a User Control to the Custom Task pane.
4. Run the project.


### Expected behavior

The FormRegion should be visible in the adjoining region of the Mail Message window.

### Actual behavior

The FormRegion is not visible in the Mail Message window.

